::'''Danae:''' ...So, let's make the most of today &mdash; oh, it looks like someone's approaching.
::'''Danae:''' Hello, you seem to be from out of town. My name's Danae, and I know this area well. Do you need a guide?
::{{DIcon|Arrow}} You're quite hospitable.
:::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_504053004-->
:::'''Danae:''' Ah, it's nothing. These are just small acts within my power. Nothing noteworthy.
:::<!--Custom String Trigger: TalkSentence_504053009-->
:::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_504053009-->
:::'''Danae:''' No need for formality. My mom taught me from a young age to be like the Holy Maiden &mdash; always lend a hand whenever possible.
:::'''Danae:''' So, my family volunteer here in our spare time, tackling chores like pulling weeds and dusting.
:::'''Danae:''' I've lived near the temple my whole life, and everyone around here knows me. If you have any doubts, you're welcome to ask the locals about me.
:::{{DIcon|Arrow}} You were raised well.
::::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_504053013-->
::::'''Danae:''' Well, my dad would be thrilled, but we're here to honor an old debt &mdash; when my mother was just a little girl, she owed a significant favor to the Holy Maiden.
::::'''Danae:''' Growing up, my mother faced severe hardships and often went without food. One particularly desperate day, she snuck into the temple hoping to find something to eat but was caught red-handed.
::::'''Danae:''' Back in those days, stealing from the temple was considered a grave offense. However, the Holy Maiden at the time chose not to punish her. After listening to her plight, she even gave my mother a bag full of sweet treats, allowing her to return home safely.
::::'''Danae:''' My mother decided to move near the temple after that. She always maintained that since she had benefitted from the Holy Maiden's generosity, it was her responsibility to continue spreading that goodness.
:::{{DIcon|Arrow}} Can you show me around?
::::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_504053018-->
::::'''Danae:''' Absolutely! I've grown up here and know every part of this place &mdash; the eaves, the columns, and even the moss on the walls.
::::'''Danae:''' See the steps at the entrance? They're a bit worn and cracked, a testament to the many pilgrims that have passed through here &mdash;
::::'''Danae:''' Legend has it that, centuries ago, the Three Titans of Fate would manifest here to respond to the prayers of the people. But those days are long gone. It's primarily the priests and the Holy Maiden who relay their prophecies now.
:::<!--Custom String Trigger: TalkSentence_504053021-->
:::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_504053021-->
:::'''Danae:''' You've traveled a long way. Why not rest up for now? If you need a guide, I'm usually around.
